UID:20f3c3ff-94d4-4fa4-8085-d03e7b12fc1d
DTSTART:20260907T120000
DTEND:20260912T210000
DESCRIPTION:Designed for anyone interested in learning the history\, anatom
 y\, and practical use of one of the most essential tools in woodworking an
 d timber processing. The course begins with a classroom session exploring 
 the history\, patterns\, and functions of different axe types. You’ll th
 en build your own custom axe handle and learn how to use a broad axe to he
 w round logs into square timbers.
SUMMARY:Axecraft - Felling\, Hewing and Axe Handling
URL;VALUE=URI:https://ce.sbwi.edu/s/courseoffering/0P0Hu000000TbwwKAC
END:VEVENT
